{
  "texts": [
    "Similar to methods discussed previously, FedIT also applies LoRA for fine-tuning FMs and leverages FedAvg for aggregating LoRA parameters.",
    "A distinctive aspect of FedIT is its utilization of structured instruction-output pairs for fine-tuning FMs.",
    "The findings from their study indicate that federated instruction tuning, offers substantial benefits over centralized training approaches.",
    "This demonstrates its potential to enhance model performance effectively, even in the presence of task diversity.",
    "E. Communication Efficient FedFMThe complexity of FMs directly translates to inflated communication overhead between FL clients and the FL server in FedFM, hindering efficient collaboration."
  ]
}